  <thing id="cDSIIShaBio" name="Shared Biology" compset="ClSpecial" description="The toilbrook cannot use her familiar to share spells or deliver touch spells for her. Instead, whenever the toilbrook consumes a food or drink (or is otherwise subject to similar effects reliant on the body, such as being inhaled or applied through the skin, up to GMs discretion) and the familiar is within the toilbrookâ€™s natural reach, she can choose to have her familiar also be affected by the effect or have her familiar be subject to its effects instead. This also applies to magical and alchemical consumables, such as Alchemy formulae and Herbalism concoctions.\n\nAt 3rd level, whenever the toilbrookâ€™s familiar is subject to such an effect delivered this way, it can decide to harmlessly store it within itselfâ€“if the effect required a saving throw (such as if it were a poison), the familiar must have succeeded its most recent saving throw against the effect to store it. The familiar can only store one such effect at a time. The familiar can deliver the stored effect as a standard action, requiring a successful melee touch attack if the creature is unwilling." summary="Your familiar is an extension of yourself, symbiotically.">
    <usesource source="pPF1e_Sph_Guile"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="ProductId" tag="DropDead" name="Drop Dead Studios" abbrev="Drop Dead Studios"/>
    <eval phase="Final"><![CDATA[
      perform hero.findchild[CompClHelp,"VaryComp.cArcFClass"].setfocus
      doneif (state.isfocus = 0)

      ~Disable familiar ablities
      perform focus.minion[ArcFamil].child[cArcFShaSp].assign[Hide.All]
      perform focus.minion[ArcFamil].child[cArcFShaSp].assign[Helper.SpcDisable]
      perform focus.minion[ArcFamil].child[cArcFDelTo].assign[Hide.All]
      perform focus.minion[ArcFamil].child[cArcFDelTo].assign[Helper.SpcDisable]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSoGBlendTrToil" name="Blended Training" compset="ClSpecial" description="The toilbrook gains 1/2 of a combat or skill talent every time she gains a class level. Toilbrooks use their operative ability modifier as their practitioner ability modifier." summary="Gain a combat or skill talent">
