  <thing id="cSoGToilBondCaul" name="Bonded Cauldron" compset="ClSpecial" description="At 1st level, the toilbrook gains the cauldron hex and begins play with a cauldron at no cost, referred to as her â€œbonded cauldronâ€. This functions as a bonded object (as a wizard of equivalent level), excluding the normal benefits of such an object. Instead, a bonded cauldron functions as an alchemy lab, and can be changed to the size of a small talisman, necklace, or similar object by touching it as a swift action (and vice versa).\n\nOnce per day, the toilbrook can spend 1 minute with her bonded cauldron experimenting with her reagents to change any number of talents gained from her apothecary ability to a different Alchemy or Herbalism sphere talent of her choice.\n\nAt 4th level, the toilbrookâ€™s bonded cauldron functions as a cauldron of brewing (Ultimate Equipment). The bonus granted by the cauldron of brewing applies to any checks made for the Alchemy or Herbalism spheres, and stacks with the bonus the bonded cauldron grants as an alchemy lab.\n\nAt 11th level, the toilbrookâ€™s bonded cauldron functions as a cauldron of plenty (Ultimate Equipment).\n\n{b}Note{/b}: You must buy the cauldron for free.">
